1
00:01:51,080 --> 00:01:52,840
PATTIA CLUB

2
00:03:34,240 --> 00:03:36,080
<i>I do not believe that my dream</i>
<i>is just an illusion,</i>

3
00:03:37,320 --> 00:03:38,960
<i>that there is no karma in this world.</i>

4
00:03:39,720 --> 00:03:42,080
<i>If the ocean is meant to spill,</i>

5
00:03:42,160 --> 00:03:46,240
<i>let the water of misery fill my heart.</i>

6
00:03:46,320 --> 00:03:48,080
<i>If far away I must go,</i>

7
00:03:48,160 --> 00:03:50,080
<i>the storms I must weather.</i>

8
00:03:50,160 --> 00:03:51,920
<i>All for freedom.</i>

9
00:03:53,280 --> 00:03:54,320
<i>By Xu Meng.</i>

10
00:04:11,440 --> 00:04:12,800
What a shocker.

11
00:04:12,880 --> 00:04:15,320
All these smoke and mirrors
in superstition.

12
00:04:15,400 --> 00:04:18,839
In the end, it was all to run away
from debt collectors.

13
00:04:18,920 --> 00:04:21,680
We should be more rational.

14
00:04:24,720 --> 00:04:26,120
What's wrong?

15
00:04:26,200 --> 00:04:27,920
We solved the case. Why the long face?

16
00:04:29,480 --> 00:04:32,480
I'm wondering if this is the only answer.

17
00:04:32,560 --> 00:04:34,320
How many answers do you need?

18
00:04:34,400 --> 00:04:36,920
Even in a comic book,
they always say there's only one truth.

19
00:04:50,360 --> 00:04:52,560
What is going on? A grand reception?

20
00:04:55,880 --> 00:04:56,720
Captain.

21
00:04:56,800 --> 00:04:57,760
WEIYANG PUBLIC SECURITY BUREAU
NANSHAN BRANCH

22
00:04:57,840 --> 00:04:58,880
Let's go.

23
00:05:00,520 --> 00:05:01,560
Captain Feng.

24
00:05:02,920 --> 00:05:03,920
What's going on?

25
00:05:05,840 --> 00:05:09,160
You two solved a big case today.

26
00:05:11,200 --> 00:05:13,880
- We solved a case?
- How did you know we solved the case?

27
00:05:13,960 --> 00:05:15,600
I haven't even told you about it yet.

28
00:05:15,680 --> 00:05:18,840
Didn't you ask me
to ambush the pickpocket?

29
00:05:22,080 --> 00:05:23,960
He did see a briefcase

30
00:05:24,040 --> 00:05:26,720
with Qingsong Cement written on it.

31
00:05:26,800 --> 00:05:28,880
<i>It was hidden inside Wu Shanlong's house.</i>

32
00:05:29,520 --> 00:05:30,440
What was inside?

33
00:05:31,080 --> 00:05:33,440
Photocopies of the tender document
on Dongshan Mine.

34
00:05:33,520 --> 00:05:36,000
Does it mean the case is solved now?

35
00:05:36,080 --> 00:05:37,920
Wu Shanlong was the whistle-blower.

36
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:41,200
Song Qingsong paid Director Li of the mine

37
00:05:41,280 --> 00:05:43,800
eight million yuan to win the bid.

38
00:05:43,880 --> 00:05:45,760
Director Li sure is cunning.

39
00:05:45,840 --> 00:05:46,920
He wants the best of both worlds.

40
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:49,840
He sold the tender
to both Song Qingsong and Cripple Du.

41
00:05:49,920 --> 00:05:51,960
And in the end, they fought.

42
00:05:52,920 --> 00:05:55,680
I get it now. Director Li
conducted this whole farce.

43
00:05:55,760 --> 00:05:57,760
He said someone stole
the tender document from the mine.

44
00:05:57,840 --> 00:05:59,600
In reality, he was
just diverting attention.

45
00:05:59,680 --> 00:06:00,640
Exactly.

46
00:06:03,160 --> 00:06:05,760
Sir. We have good news too.

47
00:06:07,720 --> 00:06:09,600
Is it about
the missing father and daughter?

48
00:06:11,960 --> 00:06:14,080
They disappeared on purpose.
We have evidence.

49
00:06:16,280 --> 00:06:17,120
Good things come in pairs.

50
00:06:17,200 --> 00:06:19,280
When I see the chief next time,

51
00:06:19,360 --> 00:06:22,000
I'll put in a good word for you two.

52
00:06:22,080 --> 00:06:25,040
Sir. There's no rush for that.

53
00:06:25,640 --> 00:06:27,920
But my secondment ends tomorrow.

54
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:29,360
I have to return to the police station.

55
00:06:29,440 --> 00:06:31,640
About my secondment evaluation report…

56
00:06:36,560 --> 00:06:38,480
Oh, He Yuanhang.

57
00:06:39,720 --> 00:06:40,720
You're crafty.

58
00:06:41,760 --> 00:06:44,880
Well, I have to bring something back
for that green-eyed colleague of mine.

59
00:06:44,960 --> 00:06:46,920
Before you return tomorrow,

60
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:48,960
bring me the case summary report,

61
00:06:49,040 --> 00:06:51,440
and you'll have your evaluation report.

62
00:06:53,360 --> 00:06:55,280
Captain Feng, do I
have to write the report too?

63
00:06:55,880 --> 00:06:59,160
The quality of your report
will affect the quality of mine.

64
00:06:59,240 --> 00:07:00,320
What?

65
00:07:01,720 --> 00:07:02,560
All the best.

66
00:07:03,800 --> 00:07:05,520
But… Captain Feng.

67
00:07:05,600 --> 00:07:07,760
Tomorrow? I've stayed up late
for a few nights already.

68
00:07:13,680 --> 00:07:15,160
He. Go back and rest up.

69
00:07:15,240 --> 00:07:16,560
I'll write the report.

70
00:07:17,920 --> 00:07:19,160
It's okay.

71
00:07:19,240 --> 00:07:21,160
Working late is part and parcel
of being a criminal detective.

72
00:07:21,240 --> 00:07:22,600
You know what? Go back and sleep.

73
00:07:22,680 --> 00:07:24,080
Drop by my place tomorrow
at noon to check my report.

74
00:07:24,160 --> 00:07:26,240
You can also taste my wife's cooking.

75
00:07:26,320 --> 00:07:28,720
- She'll make noodles for you. See you.
- Okay.

76
00:07:29,840 --> 00:07:31,720
- Drive safely!
- Okay.

77
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:05,560
Help yourself.

78
00:08:07,120 --> 00:08:07,960
Sir,

79
00:08:08,720 --> 00:08:10,800
I no longer eat coriander.

80
00:08:23,560 --> 00:08:24,640
Sir,

81
00:08:25,800 --> 00:08:27,640
you're now retired.

82
00:08:27,720 --> 00:08:29,400
Xiaohe has also grown up.

83
00:08:29,480 --> 00:08:31,880
Why don't you just enjoy your retirement?

84
00:08:34,520 --> 00:08:37,440
Are you telling me to give up?

85
00:08:39,360 --> 00:08:40,440
No.

86
00:08:41,039 --> 00:08:42,520
I'm telling you to accept
your current pace

87
00:08:42,600 --> 00:08:44,000
and you may continue to be useful.

88
00:08:44,080 --> 00:08:45,600
That's just giving up.

89
00:08:51,160 --> 00:08:52,960
Back then, you told me

90
00:08:53,840 --> 00:08:56,680
to let it go when it was time to do so
instead of dwelling on it.

91
00:08:56,760 --> 00:08:59,400
Otherwise, we would…

92
00:09:04,880 --> 00:09:05,720
Sir.

93
00:09:08,280 --> 00:09:10,040
Don't visit Yuanlongli anymore.

94
00:09:12,800 --> 00:09:14,280
I wanted to retire too back then.

95
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:15,960
But you had to drag me in.

96
00:09:16,600 --> 00:09:18,360
Now, it's the other way round.

97
00:09:18,440 --> 00:09:19,880
Ran Fangxu.

98
00:09:19,960 --> 00:09:21,600
Just be frank with me.

99
00:09:21,680 --> 00:09:23,240
Are you going to pretend
for the rest of your life

100
00:09:23,320 --> 00:09:26,280
that the June 30th case never happened?

101
00:09:31,880 --> 00:09:33,400
I made a wrong call back then.

102
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:34,960
That was on me.

103
00:09:35,760 --> 00:09:37,960
But it has been 18 years now.

104
00:09:38,040 --> 00:09:39,600
We've gone through every lead we had.

105
00:09:39,680 --> 00:09:41,080
There are no new leads.

106
00:09:41,160 --> 00:09:42,600
No new leads?

107
00:09:42,680 --> 00:09:43,880
Come here.

108
00:09:43,960 --> 00:09:45,800
- Sir.
- Come here.

109
00:09:46,440 --> 00:09:47,400
No new leads?

110
00:09:47,480 --> 00:09:48,880
No new leads? What is this?

111
00:09:49,720 --> 00:09:51,360
What is this?
What are these if not new leads?

112
00:09:51,440 --> 00:09:52,600
Sir!

113
00:09:54,440 --> 00:09:57,360
Why else do you think
I always visit Yuanlongli?

114
00:09:57,440 --> 00:10:00,160
Because I know
it has the most important lead.

115
00:10:00,240 --> 00:10:02,680
As long as Yuanlongli is still here,
the case can be solved.

116
00:10:02,760 --> 00:10:04,760
Let it go already, sir.

117
00:10:04,840 --> 00:10:07,160
No need to waste your life on one case.

118
00:10:07,240 --> 00:10:10,040
I can't! Just go away then.

119
00:10:10,120 --> 00:10:11,560
I'll just investigate it myself.

120
00:10:11,640 --> 00:10:12,480
Sir.

121
00:10:18,720 --> 00:10:19,560
Sir!

122
00:10:20,440 --> 00:10:22,640
YUANLONGLI INTERNATIONAL GARDEN

123
00:10:35,120 --> 00:10:36,480
MISSING PERSON

124
00:10:37,760 --> 00:10:40,760
Sir, what are you doing? Stop posting it.

125
00:10:41,840 --> 00:10:43,400
If you can insist on quitting,

126
00:10:43,480 --> 00:10:45,200
let me insist on investigating as well.

127
00:10:45,280 --> 00:10:46,520
We have nothing to do with each other.

128
00:10:49,840 --> 00:10:52,160
Your posters serve no purpose, sir.

129
00:10:53,520 --> 00:10:55,200
Just come back with me.

130
00:10:59,000 --> 00:11:00,160
Sir.

131
00:11:00,840 --> 00:11:01,680
Sir.

132
00:11:01,760 --> 00:11:04,200
Many things don't come with answers.

133
00:11:04,280 --> 00:11:05,560
I don't want answers.

134
00:11:05,640 --> 00:11:06,880
I want the truth.

135
00:11:06,960 --> 00:11:08,080
Let go. Let go of me.

136
00:11:08,160 --> 00:11:09,240
No!

137
00:11:09,320 --> 00:11:10,280
I won't unless you come back.

138
00:11:10,360 --> 00:11:11,560
I don't need you now. Let go.

139
00:11:11,640 --> 00:11:12,960
- No.
- Let…

140
00:11:18,560 --> 00:11:19,400
Who's there?

141
00:11:20,600 --> 00:11:22,720
Dad? What are you doing?

142
00:11:25,440 --> 00:11:26,280
Xiaohe.

143
00:11:32,600 --> 00:11:34,840
Xiaohe. Don't leave.

144
00:11:34,920 --> 00:11:36,920
Look. We're already here anyway.

145
00:11:37,000 --> 00:11:40,640
Maybe you, Uncle Ran, and I
can investigate this case together.

146
00:11:40,720 --> 00:11:42,640
I can't monitor you all the time.
I can't chain you to a post.

147
00:11:42,720 --> 00:11:43,880
I can't stop you.

148
00:11:43,960 --> 00:11:45,320
Whenever I go out,
you sneak into Yuanlongli.

149
00:11:45,400 --> 00:11:47,640
What if you fall sick again?

150
00:11:48,560 --> 00:11:50,480
Sick? Look at me.

151
00:11:50,560 --> 00:11:51,880
The very picture of health.

152
00:11:53,760 --> 00:11:57,800
Dad. I have work to do. Please

153
00:11:59,320 --> 00:12:01,040
go back with Uncle Ran.

154
00:12:01,760 --> 00:12:03,040
She's right.

155
00:12:03,120 --> 00:12:04,680
- Let's go, sir.
- Shut up.

156
00:12:05,600 --> 00:12:06,840
Xiaohe.

157
00:12:06,920 --> 00:12:08,720
You're here to find evidence

158
00:12:08,800 --> 00:12:11,200
to appeal against
Han Zi'ang's expulsion, aren't you?

159
00:12:11,280 --> 00:12:13,360
Since Uncle Ran and I are here,

160
00:12:13,440 --> 00:12:14,880
we can assist you.

161
00:12:14,960 --> 00:12:16,000
I don't need your help.

162
00:12:17,160 --> 00:12:19,440
Our investigation skills are exceptional.

163
00:12:19,520 --> 00:12:20,640
I don't need you.

164
00:12:20,720 --> 00:12:22,800
I can swear. I can swear

165
00:12:23,520 --> 00:12:26,320
that if we fail to find anything useful,

166
00:12:26,400 --> 00:12:27,520
we will leave right away.

167
00:12:27,600 --> 00:12:29,200
We won't disturb you when you work.

168
00:12:34,960 --> 00:12:36,920
What… What

169
00:12:37,760 --> 00:12:38,720
can you two do anyway?

170
00:12:39,840 --> 00:12:40,920
Right?

171
00:12:41,880 --> 00:12:43,480
I have no idea either.

172
00:12:43,560 --> 00:12:44,560
Don't play dumb.

173
00:12:48,360 --> 00:12:49,480
You know what?

174
00:12:49,560 --> 00:12:51,360
Take… Take the helmet for me.

175
00:12:53,320 --> 00:12:55,600
Stay here. Don't move. Come. Follow me.

176
00:12:56,920 --> 00:12:58,120
Where are you going?

177
00:12:58,200 --> 00:13:00,200
Just stay there. Don't move.

178
00:13:07,440 --> 00:13:08,600
MISSING PERSONS

179
00:13:12,680 --> 00:13:16,680
He Xiaohe. How can you believe
the words of a madman?

180
00:13:20,160 --> 00:13:22,160
- Run! Quick.
- What's going on?

181
00:13:22,240 --> 00:13:24,000
Quick! Quick!

182
00:13:24,080 --> 00:13:26,160
- It's dangerous. Move aside.
- Who's chasing after you?

183
00:13:26,240 --> 00:13:27,400
Careful.

184
00:13:27,480 --> 00:13:28,920
Dad! Who's pursuing you?

185
00:13:29,000 --> 00:13:30,320
- Careful.
- Dad!

186
00:13:39,400 --> 00:13:40,240
Dad!

187
00:13:47,760 --> 00:13:49,560
What are you trying to do?

188
00:13:49,640 --> 00:13:50,640
Who is pursuing you?

189
00:13:59,080 --> 00:14:02,480
Re-enactment is so effective.

190
00:14:02,560 --> 00:14:05,680
Dad. Can you stop messing around?

191
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:09,800
This is called a re-enactment.

192
00:14:09,880 --> 00:14:12,480
It's Uncle Ran's expertise.

193
00:14:12,560 --> 00:14:14,040
Re-enactment?

194
00:14:15,400 --> 00:14:18,000
Put yourself in the shoes of Han Zi'ang

195
00:14:18,080 --> 00:14:19,960
and re-enact what he did.

196
00:14:20,040 --> 00:14:23,080
Then, find clues during the process.

197
00:14:23,160 --> 00:14:27,080
You're saying
that Han Zi'ang wasn't lying in ambush.

198
00:14:27,960 --> 00:14:29,240
Someone was pursuing him.

199
00:14:30,880 --> 00:14:33,640
That was why he hid in the cupboard.

200
00:14:35,960 --> 00:14:36,840
Where's your proof?

201
00:14:40,080 --> 00:14:42,440
Uncle Ran is back. He'll answer you.

202
00:14:43,080 --> 00:14:43,920
No need for that.

203
00:14:45,080 --> 00:14:47,960
Xiaohe is smart enough
to deduce it herself.

204
00:14:49,520 --> 00:14:50,880
Did you get it then?

205
00:15:39,120 --> 00:15:40,280
Help!

206
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:43,800
Help! Help!

207
00:15:45,600 --> 00:15:47,080
Help!

208
00:15:49,880 --> 00:15:51,160
Help!

209
00:16:08,200 --> 00:16:09,200
I hear a ghost.

210
00:16:18,880 --> 00:16:19,800
Where is it?

211
00:16:20,400 --> 00:16:21,360
Over there.

212
00:16:36,200 --> 00:16:40,080
Han Zi'ang might have
been assaulted first.

213
00:16:40,160 --> 00:16:41,400
Then, he fled.

214
00:16:41,480 --> 00:16:42,600
Fearing assault,

215
00:16:42,680 --> 00:16:45,720
he acted out of self-defense
after he hid in the cupboard.

216
00:16:49,280 --> 00:16:50,160
Xiaohe.

217
00:16:51,160 --> 00:16:53,240
This is your logical deduction.

218
00:16:53,800 --> 00:16:56,920
You'll have to find the evidence yourself.

219
00:16:57,840 --> 00:16:59,480
Understood?

220
00:16:59,560 --> 00:17:00,920
You have to rely on yourself.

221
00:17:01,920 --> 00:17:05,280
Sir. You've seen how Xiaohe did just now.

222
00:17:05,359 --> 00:17:06,560
Yes.

223
00:17:07,520 --> 00:17:10,200
It exceeded my expectations.

224
00:17:10,280 --> 00:17:12,880
I know she is a capable officer,

225
00:17:13,760 --> 00:17:15,079
and I can't wait to see her
solve this case.

226
00:17:17,359 --> 00:17:19,960
Are you saying
that you still want to quit?

227
00:17:21,760 --> 00:17:22,599
Sir,

228
00:17:23,880 --> 00:17:26,280
I will wait for Xiaohe's
good news in Beijing.

229
00:17:27,560 --> 00:17:29,840
Then, I'll insert this case
into my teaching material.

230
00:17:31,000 --> 00:17:32,200
You're going back to Beijing?

231
00:17:32,880 --> 00:17:33,760
Yes.

232
00:17:50,600 --> 00:17:51,440
Dad.

233
00:17:52,520 --> 00:17:53,480
It'll be dawn soon.

234
00:17:54,840 --> 00:17:57,400
Uncle Ran has to catch the train.

235
00:18:14,760 --> 00:18:17,440
Let's go. I'll give you
a lift to the train station.

236
00:18:19,680 --> 00:18:20,560
Okay.

237
00:18:41,000 --> 00:18:42,680
AWARDED TO HE YUANHANG

238
00:18:42,760 --> 00:18:46,040
OUTSTANDING POLICE OFFICER
OF NANSHAN DISTRICT

239
00:18:48,320 --> 00:18:51,560
…THE STORMS I MUST WEATHER
ALL FOR FREEDOM. XU MENG

240
00:19:09,640 --> 00:19:13,040
YUANLONGLI JUNE 30TH CASE, SUMMARY REPORT

241
00:19:17,080 --> 00:19:19,080
<i>On August 24th, 1995,</i>

242
00:19:20,040 --> 00:19:22,360
<i>Xu Zhihong, father, and Xu Meng, daughter,</i>

243
00:19:22,440 --> 00:19:24,240
<i>were involved in an accident on Mount Wu.</i>

244
00:19:24,320 --> 00:19:26,680
<i>Xu Zhihong suffered severe injuries</i>

245
00:19:26,760 --> 00:19:27,600
- What's the matter?
- <i>and had to seek</i>

246
00:19:27,680 --> 00:19:28,840
<i>long-term medical treatment.</i>

247
00:19:29,360 --> 00:19:30,360
Dad!

248
00:19:30,920 --> 00:19:32,560
Dad! Dad!

249
00:19:33,160 --> 00:19:35,280
Save my dad. He fainted.

250
00:19:35,360 --> 00:19:37,360
Save my dad. Save my dad.

251
00:19:40,400 --> 00:19:43,200
<i>Xu Meng pawned her assets</i>
<i>and took out loans</i>

252
00:19:43,800 --> 00:19:45,200
<i>to pay for her father's medical bills.</i>

253
00:19:48,640 --> 00:19:52,920
IOU, XU MENG

254
00:20:00,960 --> 00:20:02,320
Didn't you say 8,000 yuan?

255
00:20:02,920 --> 00:20:03,960
How come there's only 6,000 yuan?

256
00:20:04,040 --> 00:20:06,280
You think I don't need
the handling fee? Huh?

257
00:20:08,200 --> 00:20:09,600
Don't just stand there.

258
00:20:11,120 --> 00:20:13,280
- Pay up now! Pay up!
- Pay up now!

259
00:20:13,360 --> 00:20:15,480
- Pay up!
- Pay up now! Pay up!

260
00:20:15,560 --> 00:20:17,160
- Pay up now!
- Pay up!

261
00:20:17,240 --> 00:20:18,240
- Pay up!
- Pay up!

262
00:20:18,320 --> 00:20:19,160
- Pay up now!
- Pay up!

263
00:20:19,240 --> 00:20:21,200
<i>As the Xus accumulated debts,</i>

264
00:20:21,280 --> 00:20:23,640
- <i>debt collectors visited them more often.</i>
- Pay up!

265
00:20:23,720 --> 00:20:24,720
<i>They shouted threats,</i>

266
00:20:25,320 --> 00:20:27,440
<i>pushing the victims into desperation.</i>

267
00:20:27,520 --> 00:20:28,840
- Pay up!
- Yes, pay up!

268
00:20:28,920 --> 00:20:30,520
- Pay up, Xu Meng!
- Xu Meng!

269
00:20:30,600 --> 00:20:33,040
- I know you're in there.
- Just come

270
00:20:34,520 --> 00:20:35,800
after me, you punks!

271
00:20:35,880 --> 00:20:37,440
Old cripple, come out now.

272
00:20:37,520 --> 00:20:39,800
- Get out now!
- Don't harass my daughter!

273
00:20:39,880 --> 00:20:41,040
- If you can stay in there,
- Stay put.

274
00:20:41,120 --> 00:20:42,920
- come out and pay up now.
- It's okay.

275
00:20:43,000 --> 00:20:44,120
- It's okay.
- Pay up!

276
00:20:44,200 --> 00:20:45,960
- Pay up!
- Bullying a girl now?

277
00:20:46,040 --> 00:20:47,920
- Come out now!
- Are you even men?

278
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:48,920
<i>Our investigation</i>

279
00:20:49,520 --> 00:20:51,880
<i>indicates that Xu Meng</i>
<i>defrauded many people</i>

280
00:20:51,960 --> 00:20:54,200
<i>by repeatedly mortgaging her property.</i>

281
00:20:55,000 --> 00:20:57,160
<i>They had the motive to run away</i>

282
00:20:57,240 --> 00:21:00,680
<i>from their debt collectors and pursuers.</i>

283
00:21:06,000 --> 00:21:07,000
Mengmeng,

284
00:21:09,160 --> 00:21:10,520
death

285
00:21:12,200 --> 00:21:13,160
is

286
00:21:14,960 --> 00:21:17,400
our only solution.

287
00:21:22,400 --> 00:21:23,360
Dad,

288
00:21:24,760 --> 00:21:26,120
I don't want to die.

289
00:21:27,840 --> 00:21:29,240
Let's run away, okay?

290
00:21:30,520 --> 00:21:32,080
We'll disappear in Weiyang.

291
00:21:35,200 --> 00:21:36,440
<i>Vanishing in Weiyang</i>

292
00:21:37,120 --> 00:21:39,600
<i>became their only way out.</i>

293
00:21:44,720 --> 00:21:47,360
<i>According to the testimony</i>
<i>of Du Mandun, a Yuanlongli resident,</i>

294
00:21:48,040 --> 00:21:50,000
<i>Xu Meng visited the New York Block</i>

295
00:21:50,080 --> 00:21:53,560
<i>to devise her escape route</i>
<i>before she executed her plan.</i>

296
00:21:58,520 --> 00:22:01,080
<i>Elevators are operated</i>
<i>by the same generic key.</i>

297
00:22:01,160 --> 00:22:03,640
<i>Having worked in Dajianchang</i>
<i>for many years,</i>

298
00:22:04,240 --> 00:22:07,240
<i>Xu Zhihong was familiar</i>
<i>with tools and could make keys.</i>

299
00:22:08,560 --> 00:22:12,360
<i>Additionally, the Xus</i>
<i>also picked the date carefully.</i>

300
00:22:12,440 --> 00:22:13,640
<i>They opted for a day when the residents</i>

301
00:22:13,720 --> 00:22:16,160
<i>would be watching the reunification</i>
<i>of Hong Kong broadcast.</i>

302
00:22:16,240 --> 00:22:20,080
<i>The absence of people on the street</i>
<i>facilitated their escape plan.</i>

303
00:22:20,160 --> 00:22:22,960
<i>At around 4:30 p.m., June 30th,</i>

304
00:22:23,040 --> 00:22:24,520
<i>Xu Meng carried Xu Zhihong on her back</i>

305
00:22:24,600 --> 00:22:26,200
<i>and arrived at Yuanlongli.</i>

306
00:22:27,080 --> 00:22:29,000
<i>At 4:38 p.m.,</i>

307
00:22:29,080 --> 00:22:32,240
<i>Xu Meng and Xu Zhihong</i>
<i>took the elevator to the 18th floor.</i>

308
00:22:33,160 --> 00:22:34,920
<i>Before they exited the elevator,</i>

309
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:37,360
<i>Xu Zhihong pressed all the buttons</i>
<i>in the elevator.</i>

310
00:22:49,880 --> 00:22:53,040
<i>After they left the elevator,</i>
<i>they split up.</i>

311
00:22:53,800 --> 00:22:56,760
<i>When the elevator stopped briefly</i>
<i>on the 17th floor,</i>

312
00:22:56,840 --> 00:22:59,640
<i>Xu Meng went to 1813</i>
<i>and hung the black cloak.</i>

313
00:23:00,520 --> 00:23:02,880
<i>Xu Zhihong then unlocked</i>
<i>the door to the elevator shaft.</i>

314
00:23:13,880 --> 00:23:15,400
<i>They worked together</i>

315
00:23:15,480 --> 00:23:17,360
<i>and dragged two wooden planks</i>
<i>with their footprints</i>

316
00:23:17,960 --> 00:23:19,560
<i>to the top of the elevator.</i>

317
00:23:25,960 --> 00:23:26,800
<i>Preliminary analysis shows</i>

318
00:23:26,880 --> 00:23:29,520
<i>that Xu Meng's and Xu Zhihong's</i>
<i>footprints, handprints</i>

319
00:23:29,600 --> 00:23:31,240
<i>collected on the elevator roof,</i>

320
00:23:31,320 --> 00:23:32,880
<i>and even the handwriting in the letter,</i>

321
00:23:32,960 --> 00:23:36,840
<i>match the ones collected</i>
<i>in their place of residence.</i>

322
00:23:37,840 --> 00:23:40,360
Dad. We must live on.

323
00:23:40,960 --> 00:23:41,880
Don't be scared.

324
00:24:00,800 --> 00:24:02,760
<i>When the elevator stopped</i>
<i>on the first floor,</i>

325
00:24:02,840 --> 00:24:05,560
<i>the Xus unlocked</i>
<i>the elevator door from the shaft</i>

326
00:24:05,640 --> 00:24:07,200
<i>and arrived at the lobby</i>
<i>on the second floor.</i>

327
00:24:32,560 --> 00:24:35,640
<i>They took the eastern staircase</i>
<i>and headed to B1.</i>

328
00:24:37,000 --> 00:24:39,080
<i>It is connected</i>
<i>to the underground car park.</i>

329
00:24:39,800 --> 00:24:41,680
<i>When Xu Meng worked in Pattia,</i>

330
00:24:41,760 --> 00:24:44,080
<i>she got her hands on the keys</i>
<i>to the underground car park.</i>

331
00:25:06,480 --> 00:25:10,080
YUANLONGLI UNDERGROUND PARKING LOT

332
00:25:38,640 --> 00:25:41,880
<i>They took the car park exit</i>
<i>and left Yuanlongli.</i>

333
00:25:42,440 --> 00:25:44,480
<i>That route was not covered</i>
<i>by security cameras.</i>

334
00:25:45,360 --> 00:25:48,920
<i>The Xus mystified their disappearance</i>

335
00:25:49,000 --> 00:25:51,120
<i>so that rumors would spread.</i>

336
00:25:51,200 --> 00:25:52,400
<i>The superstitious beliefs</i>

337
00:25:52,480 --> 00:25:55,040
<i>would also deter their debt collectors</i>
<i>from coming closer,</i>

338
00:25:55,120 --> 00:25:57,760
<i>thereby giving up on pursuing them.</i>

339
00:26:01,840 --> 00:26:05,120
<i>In conclusion,</i>
<i>this is a premeditated, voluntary</i>

340
00:26:05,200 --> 00:26:07,320
<i>missing person case motivated</i>
<i>by the desire to evade debt collection.</i>

341
00:26:16,280 --> 00:26:18,320
<i>Should any request to locate them be made,</i>

342
00:26:18,400 --> 00:26:20,440
<i>we recommend requesting the city council</i>

343
00:26:20,520 --> 00:26:22,640
<i>to enlarge the search scope.</i>

344
00:26:38,720 --> 00:26:40,640
WRITTEN BY, TIME

345
00:26:50,560 --> 00:26:52,560
<i>Written by Ran Fangxu,</i>

346
00:26:54,040 --> 00:26:55,040
<i>He Yuanhang.</i>

347
00:26:56,080 --> 00:26:57,880
WRITTEN BY: RAN FANGXU, HE YUANHANG
TIME: JULY 5TH, 1997

348
00:27:18,200 --> 00:27:19,200
Hi, Uncle Ran.

349
00:27:19,280 --> 00:27:21,200
- Hi, Xiaohe.
- You're here.

350
00:27:21,920 --> 00:27:22,880
Allow me to introduce him.

351
00:27:22,960 --> 00:27:25,200
Ran. R-A-N.

352
00:27:25,280 --> 00:27:26,480
Ran Fangxu.

353
00:27:26,560 --> 00:27:30,000
And this one is my wife,
Sun Yun. Director Sun.

354
00:27:30,080 --> 00:27:32,240
- Hi, Mrs. He.
- Hi, Ran.

355
00:27:33,200 --> 00:27:35,480
- This is for you.
- You didn't have to.

356
00:27:35,560 --> 00:27:38,240
Come in. Let me serve the noodles.

357
00:27:39,080 --> 00:27:40,040
Take the shoes.

358
00:27:41,480 --> 00:27:44,880
- Uncle Ran, your sandals.
- Thank you, Xiaohe. This is for you.

359
00:27:45,480 --> 00:27:47,000
What is that?

360
00:27:48,440 --> 00:27:49,720
Oh. A doll.

361
00:27:49,800 --> 00:27:51,400
Thank you, Uncle Ran.

362
00:27:54,360 --> 00:27:56,560
They both have something. Is this mine?

363
00:28:01,800 --> 00:28:04,480
A freebie when I bought
the gift for your wife.

364
00:28:05,400 --> 00:28:07,120
A freebie? I like it.

365
00:28:09,720 --> 00:28:10,560
It suits me.

366
00:28:11,240 --> 00:28:12,640
Come. Come.

367
00:28:18,880 --> 00:28:19,960
Here.

368
00:28:20,880 --> 00:28:21,720
Take a seat.

369
00:28:23,720 --> 00:28:25,680
Make sure you don't tell my wife later

370
00:28:25,760 --> 00:28:26,960
that I'm going back to the police station.

371
00:28:27,560 --> 00:28:28,960
But aren't you going back tomorrow?

372
00:28:29,800 --> 00:28:32,360
- You haven't told your wife?
- The noodles are ready.

373
00:28:33,920 --> 00:28:34,760
Come.

374
00:28:35,960 --> 00:28:37,240
How nice.

375
00:28:38,200 --> 00:28:41,720
Listen. My wife cooked
a whole table of food for you.

376
00:28:41,800 --> 00:28:42,680
Sorry for the hassle, Mrs. He.

377
00:28:42,760 --> 00:28:44,160
Not a hassle at all. Take a seat.

378
00:28:44,240 --> 00:28:45,200
Okay.

379
00:28:47,360 --> 00:28:48,560
It smells divine.

380
00:28:49,120 --> 00:28:52,640
Dad told me
Uncle Ran likes coriander best.

381
00:28:52,720 --> 00:28:54,720
I washed them all myself.

382
00:28:55,800 --> 00:28:57,120
Thank you, Xiaohe.

383
00:28:58,360 --> 00:28:59,640
Come. Let's have a toast.

384
00:28:59,720 --> 00:29:02,280
- Welcome to our humble abode, Ran.
- Thank you, Mrs. He.

385
00:29:02,360 --> 00:29:04,120
- You're welcome.
- Welcome.

386
00:29:08,240 --> 00:29:09,080
He Yuanhang.

387
00:29:09,880 --> 00:29:11,520
Are you hiding something from me?

388
00:29:14,560 --> 00:29:16,280
Why would I be hiding something from you?

389
00:29:17,360 --> 00:29:19,640
Didn't you say Ran was your apprentice?

390
00:29:19,720 --> 00:29:22,320
So isn't it a bit inappropriate for him
to call me Mrs. He?

391
00:29:24,720 --> 00:29:26,040
It sounds younger that way.

392
00:29:26,120 --> 00:29:28,000
Madam Sun sounds way older.

393
00:29:28,080 --> 00:29:31,040
Lie. Lie more.

394
00:29:31,760 --> 00:29:34,200
Ran is a top scorer from PPSUC.

395
00:29:34,280 --> 00:29:36,120
You're here for a secondment.

396
00:29:36,200 --> 00:29:38,120
There's no way he's your apprentice.

397
00:29:39,080 --> 00:29:40,320
Right, Ran?

398
00:29:45,920 --> 00:29:47,400
He

399
00:29:48,400 --> 00:29:49,600
is indeed my mentor.

400
00:29:53,120 --> 00:29:54,400
Did you hear that?

401
00:29:55,480 --> 00:29:57,720
Feng did this?

402
00:30:00,520 --> 00:30:02,240
- Eat more.
- Thank you, Mrs. He.

403
00:30:02,320 --> 00:30:05,560
You can hardly find a down-to-earth
young man nowadays.

404
00:30:06,160 --> 00:30:09,080
You're smart, capable,
and have the required qualification.

405
00:30:09,160 --> 00:30:12,120
I'm sure your workplace
will invest a lot in you.

406
00:30:13,240 --> 00:30:15,440
He will stay at the criminal department.

407
00:30:15,520 --> 00:30:19,000
Ran, you will support him, won't you?

408
00:30:21,840 --> 00:30:23,760
Actually, the criminal department
has a heavy workload.

409
00:30:23,840 --> 00:30:25,760
Even heavier than a bank.

410
00:30:25,840 --> 00:30:26,760
Xiaohe is still young.

411
00:30:26,840 --> 00:30:28,080
She needs her parents.

412
00:30:28,160 --> 00:30:29,800
Yes, Dad.

413
00:30:29,880 --> 00:30:31,280
I need my parents.

414
00:30:31,880 --> 00:30:32,720
For what?

415
00:30:35,360 --> 00:30:37,720
The biggest thing a father can do
for his children

416
00:30:37,800 --> 00:30:39,320
is to be a great role model,

417
00:30:39,400 --> 00:30:41,840
not to keep them company.

418
00:30:44,520 --> 00:30:45,720
Don't you agree, Ran?

419
00:30:47,800 --> 00:30:50,240
Yes. You're right.

420
00:30:50,320 --> 00:30:51,480
Oh, Ran.

421
00:30:52,200 --> 00:30:53,520
Are you single?

422
00:30:53,600 --> 00:30:55,760
I know many single women in my work.

423
00:30:55,840 --> 00:30:56,720
Do you want me to introduce
some of them to you?

424
00:30:56,800 --> 00:30:59,680
Uncle Ran doesn't need that.

425
00:30:59,760 --> 00:31:01,400
I know Ms. Qiao.

426
00:31:01,480 --> 00:31:03,080
She likes Uncle Ran.

427
00:31:03,160 --> 00:31:05,160
She's so pretty.

428
00:31:05,880 --> 00:31:08,280
Where does she work? She's quick.

429
00:31:09,200 --> 00:31:10,160
Mrs. He.

430
00:31:10,240 --> 00:31:12,040
I just arrived in Weiyang.

431
00:31:12,120 --> 00:31:13,160
I just want to focus on my work.

432
00:31:13,240 --> 00:31:15,400
I don't have time for anything else.

433
00:31:18,240 --> 00:31:19,800
Sir.

434
00:31:20,760 --> 00:31:22,920
How did the case report go?

435
00:31:23,520 --> 00:31:25,320
Oh. It's almost done.

436
00:31:25,400 --> 00:31:27,280
But I'm not so sure about certain details.

437
00:31:27,360 --> 00:31:28,880
Can you help me?

438
00:31:28,960 --> 00:31:31,640
- You can read it after the meal.
- It won't take long. Work comes first.

439
00:31:31,720 --> 00:31:32,880
Come. Take a look.

440
00:31:32,960 --> 00:31:34,840
We'll be back soon. Soon.

441
00:31:42,960 --> 00:31:44,760
Stop playing with it. Eat.

442
00:31:55,040 --> 00:31:58,120
SHE LEFT A LETTER. "I DO NOT BELIEVE
THAT MY DREAM IS JUST AN ILLUSION…"

443
00:32:03,600 --> 00:32:07,400
Where do you think they are right now?

444
00:32:11,280 --> 00:32:13,120
It's the first case of your life.

445
00:32:13,200 --> 00:32:16,360
Are you lamenting the fact
that you can't find them?

446
00:32:18,960 --> 00:32:22,360
No. Humans can adapt to many things.

447
00:32:22,960 --> 00:32:25,160
As long as they live a good life
where they are right now.

448
00:32:32,760 --> 00:32:35,160
It's good. Very thorough.

449
00:32:35,240 --> 00:32:37,640
I wouldn't have been able
to word it so vividly.

450
00:32:38,240 --> 00:32:40,680
Of course. I'm your mentor after all.

451
00:32:41,480 --> 00:32:43,320
Mr. He Yuanhang.

452
00:32:43,400 --> 00:32:45,440
Humility is often a virtue.

453
00:32:45,520 --> 00:32:47,120
Mr. Ran Fangxu.

454
00:32:47,200 --> 00:32:49,320
Humility in excess is arrogance.

455
00:32:54,320 --> 00:32:55,680
WRITTEN BY: RAN FANGXU, HE YUANHANG
TIME: JULY 5TH, 1997

456
00:33:01,120 --> 00:33:03,600
- What's wrong?
- The name sequence is wrong.

457
00:33:03,680 --> 00:33:05,120
No need for that.

458
00:33:05,200 --> 00:33:06,200
- He.
- It's fine.

459
00:33:06,280 --> 00:33:07,880
We must be truthful.

460
00:33:07,960 --> 00:33:10,240
I am being truthful. Listen.

461
00:33:10,320 --> 00:33:11,280
Investigation-wise,

462
00:33:11,360 --> 00:33:13,680
you are the main contributor
who solved this case.

463
00:33:13,760 --> 00:33:17,120
And in terms of your career,
you will stay in the criminal department.

464
00:33:17,200 --> 00:33:18,920
Whereas I will return
to the police station.

465
00:33:19,000 --> 00:33:20,520
- The sequence of our names
- Sir.

466
00:33:20,600 --> 00:33:21,600
- does not matter.
- Sir.

467
00:33:21,680 --> 00:33:23,440
Let me finish. It does not matter.

468
00:33:23,520 --> 00:33:25,800
Tomorrow, I'll take the evaluation
report Captain Feng gives me

469
00:33:25,880 --> 00:33:27,200
and return to the police station.

470
00:33:27,280 --> 00:33:30,920
I want to show Qu Dahai just how…

471
00:33:52,440 --> 00:33:55,000
- Why didn't you tell me?
- I tried.

472
00:33:55,080 --> 00:33:57,040
- What did you say?
- Sir.

473
00:34:09,880 --> 00:34:11,080
My wife is like this.

474
00:34:11,800 --> 00:34:13,440
She gets angry very fast,
but she also forgets about it very fast.

475
00:34:13,520 --> 00:34:14,880
She'll be fine in a few days.

476
00:34:16,120 --> 00:34:17,239
He.

477
00:34:18,520 --> 00:34:20,960
Have you ever considered staying?

478
00:34:23,400 --> 00:34:24,520
Of course I have.

479
00:34:25,120 --> 00:34:26,760
Why didn't you wait for me?

480
00:34:26,840 --> 00:34:28,800
I want to see Uncle Ran off too.

481
00:34:28,880 --> 00:34:31,560
Naughty girl! The floor is cold.
You came out without shoes.

482
00:34:31,639 --> 00:34:33,440
Wear your shoes. Come.

483
00:34:35,840 --> 00:34:37,159
You're here anyway.

484
00:34:37,239 --> 00:34:39,199
Why should I wear my shoes?

485
00:34:39,280 --> 00:34:41,440
Look at you. Your soles are dirty.

486
00:34:41,520 --> 00:34:43,360
When mom sees that, she'll scold you.

487
00:34:43,440 --> 00:34:44,760
Wash your feet when you go back.

488
00:34:44,840 --> 00:34:46,600
Okay. You have to teach me

489
00:34:46,679 --> 00:34:48,760
the 10th move of the evil-subduing
fist technique tonight.

490
00:34:48,840 --> 00:34:50,120
Of course.

491
00:34:51,719 --> 00:34:52,960
You see.

492
00:34:53,040 --> 00:34:55,719
I don't have a huge ambition.

493
00:34:55,800 --> 00:34:57,000
I understand.

494
00:34:57,080 --> 00:34:58,200
He.

495
00:35:00,960 --> 00:35:02,240
This isn't half bad either.

496
00:35:06,920 --> 00:35:08,240
Come. Let's see Uncle Ran off.

497
00:35:08,960 --> 00:35:11,400
Uncle Ran. Let me sing you a song.

498
00:35:11,480 --> 00:35:13,520
My class sings this song when someone

499
00:35:13,600 --> 00:35:15,320
- is transferring to another school.
- Sure.

500
00:35:16,160 --> 00:35:18,240
<i>Traveling the world</i>

501
00:35:18,320 --> 00:35:19,560
<i>The journey</i>

502
00:35:19,640 --> 00:35:20,640
<i>Is endless</i>

503
00:35:20,720 --> 00:35:22,440
<i>Lost and aimless</i>

504
00:35:22,520 --> 00:35:24,440
<i>One village after another</i>

505
00:35:24,520 --> 00:35:26,520
<i>Staring at the setting sun</i>

506
00:35:26,600 --> 00:35:27,560
<i>Sinking</i>

507
00:35:27,640 --> 00:35:28,640
<i>And rising again</i>

508
00:35:28,720 --> 00:35:29,640
<i>The world</i>

509
00:35:29,720 --> 00:35:30,640
<i>Remains unchanged</i>

510
00:35:30,720 --> 00:35:32,480
<i>The time remains long</i>

511
00:35:53,000 --> 00:35:55,160
You came all the way to Weiyang.

512
00:35:55,920 --> 00:35:59,040
And those old things in the bureau
won't even come to send you off.

513
00:35:59,120 --> 00:36:01,320
They are so heartless.

514
00:36:02,240 --> 00:36:04,320
Sir. They have work to do.

515
00:36:04,400 --> 00:36:06,000
They are in the special task force.

516
00:36:11,720 --> 00:36:13,640
WEIYANG STATION

517
00:36:13,720 --> 00:36:14,560
We're here.

518
00:36:19,160 --> 00:36:22,600
Xiaohe. Let me speak
to Uncle Ran privately.

519
00:36:40,920 --> 00:36:44,240
Have you ever considered staying?

520
00:36:46,920 --> 00:36:48,640
WEIYANG

521
00:36:52,120 --> 00:36:53,320
Maybe next time.

522
00:36:55,280 --> 00:36:56,160
I should go now.

523
00:37:04,880 --> 00:37:07,160
Xiaohe. I'm leaving now.

524
00:37:17,200 --> 00:37:18,720
She doesn't want you to leave either.

525
00:37:19,640 --> 00:37:20,920
But she's stubborn.

526
00:37:21,600 --> 00:37:22,880
She won't show it.

527
00:37:26,320 --> 00:37:27,240
Sir.

528
00:37:28,000 --> 00:37:28,920
Take care.

529
00:38:18,960 --> 00:38:20,680
Why did you leave so soon?

530
00:38:22,360 --> 00:38:24,600
You heartless creature.

531
00:38:24,680 --> 00:38:26,760
You won't even let me finish
what I want to say.

532
00:38:41,160 --> 00:38:44,560
Are you scolding the train or me? Sir.

533
00:39:01,360 --> 00:39:02,560
You decided to stay?

534
00:39:05,640 --> 00:39:06,480
Sir,

535
00:39:07,000 --> 00:39:08,440
you're right.

536
00:39:08,520 --> 00:39:09,840
I cannot run away from it forever.

537
00:39:10,480 --> 00:39:13,200
I'm staying to investigate
the June 30th case with you.

538
00:39:14,360 --> 00:39:16,480
You finally got it through
your thick head.

539
00:39:16,560 --> 00:39:19,040
I knew it. All these years in Beijing

540
00:39:19,120 --> 00:39:21,440
and you still care about this case. Right?

541
00:39:24,200 --> 00:39:26,320
Given your old age,

542
00:39:26,400 --> 00:39:28,240
without my assistance,

543
00:39:28,320 --> 00:39:30,120
you probably
won't be able to find anything.

544
00:39:30,960 --> 00:39:32,080
Good boy.

545
00:39:32,160 --> 00:39:33,840
You still care about me, after all.

546
00:39:34,960 --> 00:39:37,000
Xiaohe. Look.

547
00:39:37,080 --> 00:39:38,360
Guess who's back?

548
00:39:39,040 --> 00:39:41,640
Look. This is my apprentice.

549
00:39:41,720 --> 00:39:42,960
Ran Fangxu.

550
00:39:43,720 --> 00:39:47,120
When we work together, we are invincible.

551
00:39:47,760 --> 00:39:49,920
Peculiar cases or cold cases,

552
00:39:50,000 --> 00:39:51,400
they are nothing to us.

553
00:39:51,480 --> 00:39:54,960
Let alone a tiny Yuanlongli case. Right?

554
00:39:56,880 --> 00:39:57,720
He's my apprentice.

555
00:39:58,680 --> 00:39:59,520
My apprentice.

556
00:40:32,080 --> 00:40:33,200
Wait.

557
00:40:34,080 --> 00:40:36,240
I'm sure you've never left.

558
00:40:37,240 --> 00:40:40,000
When Mrs. Feng's grandson,
Ma Qiang's nephew,

559
00:40:40,080 --> 00:40:43,840
and Li Tieling's son
went missing in Yuanlongli,

560
00:40:43,920 --> 00:40:46,280
you helped me locate them.

561
00:40:47,840 --> 00:40:51,080
Sir. You got it wrong.

562
00:40:51,160 --> 00:40:52,720
I've been teaching in Beijing.

563
00:41:03,800 --> 00:41:04,920
This doesn't make sense.

564
00:41:06,160 --> 00:41:08,040
The train had already departed.

565
00:41:08,120 --> 00:41:10,520
You took the train and left
a long time ago.

566
00:41:10,600 --> 00:41:11,880
How did you return?

567
00:41:11,960 --> 00:41:14,080
How did the train return?
